MARCInd1Label: Type of time period in subfield $b or $c
RDA Registry Label:
has coverage of content [timespan]
identifier for timespan [nomen]
[nomen] access point for timespan of
[nomen] scheme of nomen
Recording Method:
mint IRI for timespan
mint nomen for has identifier of timespan
map $a as access point for timespan of nomen
give scheme of nomen (string)
Justification for Mapping:
Phase I - MARC table code as identifier of timespan, use nomen to capture scheme of nomen
 --LNA 2025-03-10
Transformation Notes:
[work] -->rdawoP10216-->[mint coverage timespan]
[timespan]-->rdatoP70015-->[mint nomen for identifier of timespan]
{nomen]-->rdanP80026-->"contents of $a"
[nomen]-->rdanP80069-->"MARC 045 Time Period Code" 

 --LNA 2025-03-10

MARCInd1Label: Type of time period in subfield $b or $c
RDA Registry Label:
has date of work [timespan]
has identifier for timespan [nomen]
[nomen] access point for timespan of
[nomen] scheme of nomen
Recording Method:
Mint IRI for timespan
mint nomen as ideentifier of timespan
map $a as access point for timespan of noment
give scheme of nomen (string)
Justification for Mapping:
Phase I - MARC table code as identifier of timespan, use nomen to capture scheme of nomen.  

For printed music and sound recordings, date of composition of the work is defined as the time period of coverage, which better maps to Date of work.   
 --LNA 2025-03-10
Transformation Notes:
[work] -->rdawoP10219-->[mint date of work timespan]
[timespan]-->rdatoP70015-->[mint nomen for identifier of timespan]
{nomen]-->rdanP80026-->"contents of $a"
[nomen]-->rdanP80069-->"MARC 045 Time Period Code" 

 --LNA 2025-03-10
Problems with Mapping:
Date of work would be appropriate for the date a naturally occurring object originated, but there is no MARC data to separate naturally occurring objects from artifacts, which better map to "has coverage of content".
 --LNA 2025-03-10

MARCInd1ValueLabel: Single date/time OR Multiple single dates/times
MARCSubfieldLabel:
b: Formatted 9999 B.C. through C.E. time period (R)
c: Formatted pre-9999 B.C. time period
RDA Registry Label:
has coverage of content
has access point for timespan
has nomen string
scheme of nomen
Recording Method:
rdawoP10216 - mint IRI for timespan
rdatoP70015 - mint IRI for nomen for access point
rdanP80068 - date from b or c structured, as nomen string
rdanP80069 - scheme of nomen IRI https://id.loc.gov/datatypes/edtf/EDTF-level0.html

 --LNA 2025-03-10
Justification for Mapping:
Description of "coverage" for 045 for various formats seems to map most simply to "has coverage of content" in RDA

Indicator 0 or 1 indicates that one or more subfields b (B.C. 9999 through C.E) or c (B.C. before 9999) contain a single date that is a timespan associated with the coverage of content

 --LNA 2025-03-10.
Transformation Notes:
Coders - please fill in the path based on recording method - read the LC documentation and note that subfield b begins with a code.  "d" means Common Era and should just be discarded, taking the date/time string following it as the nomen string.  "c" means B.C. and should become a minus before the date/time string.  Other than that, hopefully you can format the dates in EDTF without any trouble.  

 --LNA 2025-03-10

MARCSubfieldLabel:
b: Formatted 9999 B.C. through C.E. time period (R)
c: Formatted pre-9999 B.C. time period
RDA Registry Label:
has coverage of content
has access point for timespan
has nomen string
scheme of nomen
Recording Method:
rdawoP10216 - mint IRI for timespan
rdatoP70015 - mint IRI for nomen for access point
rdanP80068 - date from b or c structured, as nomen string
rdanP80069 - scheme of nomen IRI https://id.loc.gov/datatypes/edtf/EDTF-level0.html

 --LNA 2025-03-10
Justification for Mapping:
Description of "coverage" for 045 for various formats seems to map most simply to "has coverage of content" in RDA

Indicator 2 indicates there should be two subfields (b, c, or possibly a combination) in the tag that express a date range.  This range can be formatted in EDTF using a / between the date expressionss.  

 --LNA 2025-03-10
Transformation Notes:
Coders, you will need to examine both subfields (2 b, 2c, or possibly a c and a b) and determine which date is earliest, then construct a date range in EDTF as the nomen string for the timespan.  There should only be two for this tag!

 --LNA 2025-03-10
